cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.GT. 

The paper proposes the use of intelligent agents to guide taxi drivers in an urban taxi service, drawing from AI literature on multiagent planning. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.MA are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves modeling the system as a Markov chain and a Markov decision process, which falls under cs.SY. The use of Nash equilibrium policy to solve the game falls under cs.GT. Finally, the paper proposes a solution to minimize wastage of resources, which could fall under cs.LG.
